# Shell + Node helper scripts MUST be LF on every platform.
# They run under bash (Git Bash on Windows, /bin/bash on macOS/Linux) and node;
# a CRLF line ending makes bash fail with `bad interpreter: /usr/bin/env bash^M`
# or `$'\r': command not found` on macOS/Linux. Pin them to LF regardless of a
# developer's core.autocrlf setting so a Windows commit can never break a Mac checkout.
*.sh   text eol=lf
*.bash text eol=lf
*.mjs  text eol=lf

# Markdown / JSON: normalize to LF in the repo (functionally irrelevant, keeps diffs clean).
*.md   text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf
